{"name": "django-yarnpkg", "metadata": {"name": "django-yarnpkg", "version": "6.1.2", "classifiers": ["Framework :: Django", "Programming Language :: JavaScript", "Programming Language :: Python", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": "https://edugit.org/AlekSIS/libs/django-yarnpkg", "license": "Apache-2.0", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["django"], "summary": "Integrate django with yarnpkg", "upload_time": 1704898405}, "documentation": ["# Django-yarnpkg\n\nEasy way to use [yarnpkg](https://yarnpkg.com/) with your [Django](https://www.djangoproject.com/) project.\n\nThis is a fork of `django-bower <https://github.com/nvbn/django-bower>` by Vladimir Iakovlev.\n\nRead full documentation on [read-the-docs](https://django-yarnpkg.readthedocs.io/en/latest/).\n\n## Installation\n\nInstall django-yarnpkg package:\n\n```bash\npip install django-yarnpkg\n```\n\nAdd django-bower to `INSTALLED_APPS` in your settings:\n\n```python\n'django_yarnpkg',\n```\n\nAdd staticfinder to `STATICFILES_FINDERS`:\n\n```python\n'django_yarnpkg.finders.NodeModulesFinder',\n```\n\nSpecify path to components root (you need to use an absolute path):\n\n```python\nNODE_MODULES_ROOT = os.path.join(BASE_DIR, 'node_modules')\n```\n\nIf you need, you can manually set the path to yarnpkg:\n\n```python\nYARN_PATH = '/usr/bin/yarnpkg'\n```\n\nYou can see an example settings file in [example project](https://edugit.org/AlekSIS/libs/django-yarnpkg/blob/master/example/example/settings.py).\n\n## Usage\n\nSpecify `YARN_INSTALLED_APPS` in settings, like:\n\n```python\nYARN_INSTALLED_APPS = (\n    'bootstrap@^4.4.1',\n    'underscore@^1.6.1',\n)\n```\n\nDownload yarn packages with the management command:\n\n```bash\n./manage.py yarn install\n```\n\nAdd scripts in the template, like:\n\n```html+django\n{% load static %}\n<script type=\"text/javascript\" src='{% static 'jquery/dist/jquery.js' %}'></script>\n```\n\nIn production you need to call `yarnpkg install` before `collectstatic`:\n\n```bash\n./manage.py yarn install\n./manage.py collectstatic\n```\n\nIf you need to pass arguments to yarnpkg, like `--flat`, use:\n\n```bash\n./manage.py yarn install -- --flat\n```\n\nYou can call yarnpkg commands like `info` and `update` with:\n\n```bash\n./manage.py yarn info backbone\n./manage.py yarn update\n```\n\n## Python 3 support\n\ndjango-yarnpkg supports python 3.3+\n"], "modules": [{"name": "django_yarnpkg.shortcuts", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "django_yarnpkg.shortcuts.is_executable", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "path", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Check file is executable"]}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "django_yarnpkg.templatetags", "documentation": ["-*- coding: utf-8 -*-"], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "django_yarnpkg.templatetags.yarn", "documentation": ["-*- coding: utf-8 -*-"], "functions": [{"name": "django_yarnpkg.templatetags.yarn.tags", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "context", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "args", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "type", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "django_yarnpkg.templatetags.yarn.yarn_styles", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "context", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "*args", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "django_yarnpkg.templatetags.yarn.yarn_scripts", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "context", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "*args", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [{"name": "django_yarnpkg.templatetags.yarn.register", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "django_yarnpkg.templatetags.yarn.style_template", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "django_yarnpkg.templatetags.yarn.script_template", "type": null, "docu